1
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,360
Mr. Warat, how is Ms. Kluay?

2
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,560
Right now, I still can't give an answer.

3
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:50,600
But I'm certain

4
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,200
Ms. Kluay will be safe.

5
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,880
Yes.

6
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:56,040
With the utmost respect, sir,

7
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:59,000
both Ms. Kluay and Mr. Arnon
experienced similar incidents like this.

8
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,280
From now on, we can't
trust anyone anymore, Mr. Warat.

9
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,320
If I find out who did this,

10
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:07,960
I won't let them get away with it.

11
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,240
And if the lab results come back

12
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:14,240
showing that both Ms. Kluay and Mr. Arnon
were poisoned with the same substance,

13
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,840
I think it won't be difficult
to catch the culprit.

14
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:31,760
Oh, Mr. Supol, what brings you here?

15
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,400
Didn't Mr. Arnon already leave?

16
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,120
Mr. Chatchai.

17
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:38,000
I thought your face looked familiar
when I passed the ER,

18
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,240
but I thought I was mistaken.

19
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,440
Mm.

20
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,560
If you feel uncomfortable
telling me, that's fine.

21
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,440
I'll eventually find out.

22
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,480
If I really want to know, I can just ask.

23
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:52,160
But be careful. I might end up asking

24
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,280
someone you wouldn't want to find out.

25
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,680
Again?

26
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,800
Poisoned again? Are you kidding me?

27
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,400
Why would I joke about this?
If you don't believe me,

28
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,440
go see Kluay's condition for yourself.

29
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,960
Is it that serious?

30
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,920
What exactly is going on?

31
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,399
As far as I know,
she's in a life-or-death situation.

32
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,920
But there's something
even more interesting.

33
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,680
Last night,
Kluay and Mr. Warat went to your house.

34
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,840
What were those two doing there?

35
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,240
Mr. Sin's picture?

36
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,280
Did you come to bring something
for Sin, Mr. Chatchai?

37
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:47,920
Hello.

38
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,480
Please wait a moment.
Anong is getting it ready.

39
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,120
That's alright. I'm not in a hurry.

40
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,240
Actually, Sin

41
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,800
can be quite picky sometimes.

42
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,320
Oh, Mr. Sin said he wanted
to return to the office,

43
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,680
so he asked for some work clothes.

44
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,240
Hm. Hard-working, huh?

45
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,960
I was just talking to Mr. Warat about him.

46
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:12,720
I was wondering
when Sin would come back to work.

47
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:15,920
You met Mr. Warat too?

48
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,680
Yes. Yesterday evening,

49
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,840
Mr. Warat came
to have dinner here with Kluay.

50
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,920
Why didn't Aunt Anong mention that?

51
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,960
When I called her to bring you my clothes,

52
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,600
she didn't say those two came by.

53
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,840
That's the strange part.

54
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,240
I was wondering
why you didn't know anything about it.

55
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,320
Is something wrong?

56
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,200
For the past few days,
Aunt Anong has been acting strangely.

57
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:38,240
I told you

58
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,520
you should forgive Mr. Arnon.

59
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,400
Arnon was poisoned,

60
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,280
and now Kluay too.

61
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,320
What does that have to do with your aunt?

62
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,560
Maybe nothing. But do you remember

63
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,040
when I told you

64
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,480
I wanted Aunt Anong
to see your psychiatrist friend?

65
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,920
Of course I remember.

66
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,680
I already told the doctor about it.

67
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,960
But even if he weren't my friend,

68
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:03,320
no doctor would reveal
a patient's secrets.

69
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:07,000
You can rest assured. Besides,

70
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:09,080
these days,
everyone goes to see a psychiatrist.

71
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,600
It's not unusual anymore.

72
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,520
Do you want me
to talk to your aunt for you?

73
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,520
No need.

74
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,360
She isn't someone
who opens up to people easily.

75
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,360
Right, I forgot about that.

76
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:24,080
But trust me.
Take your aunt to see a doctor.

77
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:31,520
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

78
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,840
Ms. Ampha.

79
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,960
Don't cry.

80
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,960
Thank you, Ms. Ampha.

81
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,080
Ms. Ampha.

82
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,480
Ms. Ampha.

83
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,360
Are you okay?

84
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,400
- I'll go get a doctor.
- Oh.

85
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,760
Mr. Warat.

86
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,720
Ms. Ampha was the one who saved me.

87
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,720
I… I felt that too.

88
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,680
I could see that she was in pain.

89
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,080
She looked very sad.

90
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,880
But now I don't know where she's gone.

91
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,960
Okay. We'll help her.

92
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,480
But right now, we need to make sure

93
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,360
you're safe. Okay?

94
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,360
I should have trusted the sign you saw.

95
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:52,400
We should have been more careful.

96
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,400
If I hadn't drunk that glass of water…

97
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,760
Are you sure…

98
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,800
that it was the water
from Mr. Sarut's house?

99
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,720
I saw an evil spirit

100
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,280
inside Ms. Anong.

101
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,320
At the time, I thought

102
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,360
we were almost finished
with the investigation,

103
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,440
so I didn't want anything to interrupt it.

104
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,360
Then, the one who poisoned you…

105
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,000
was Ms. Anong.

106
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,760
She poisoned you

107
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,679
and poisoned Mr. Arnon.

108
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:42,240
But what reason would that woman have
to do something like that?

109
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,040
REGISTRATION

110
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:52,280
Good. Now we'll have records of
everyone going in and out of Baan Saeng.

111
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:54,880
Yes. Not only those who come
to visit the children,

112
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,480
even if it's just for small errands,

113
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,120
I will also record
their names and surnames

114
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,160
and ask to see their ID cards too.

115
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,800
That's good.

116
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:07,360
I'm planning to take
two or three days off.

117
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,000
But I'll still come and go.

118
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,280
Is that okay with you and your mom?

119
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,960
Oh, Arnon.

120
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,680
Mom and I should be the ones asking you

121
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,120
if it's convenient for you.

122
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,800
Mama Toi doesn't want to bother you.

123
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:20,560
- Hey.
- Just recently,

124
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:23,720
she even went to the market
to prepare food for her new son.

125
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:26,040
Don't worry about that.

126
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,520
Who knows.
I might even ask for a job here.

127
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,880
- Mm.
- Well.

128
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,320
Now that there are no more bad things,

129
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,640
Baan Saeng really is
a wonderful place to live.

130
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,960
The kids here are lovely.

131
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:40,360
The volunteers are all kind.

132
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,680
And the atmosphere

133
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:46,000
is filled with Mama Toi's love.

134
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,080
The security guard out front

135
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,600
- likes to crack jokes too.
- Mm.

136
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:54,440
And the housekeeper
often buys snacks for everyone.

137
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,640
There's nowhere happier than here.

138
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,720
That's all?

139
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,600
Yeah. Did I say something wrong?

140
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,480
Yes, you did. What about me?

141
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,400
For me,

142
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,400
you're not in Baan Saeng.

143
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,800
Oh? Then why would you say that?

144
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,400
Because you are right here.

145
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,280
Making cheap jokes now, huh?

146
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,480
I can do even cheaper ones.

147
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,240
- Ah.
- Here, your reward.

148
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,160
- Is it good?
- It's delicious.

149
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,000
- Som, Arnon.
- Hm?

150
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,720
Please look at this.

151
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,240
Whose is it?

152
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:43,800
He already left.
I called out but he didn't respond.

153
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,840
What did he come here for?

154
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,520
He came asking for Kluay.

155
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,320
But I told him
that she isn't staying here for now,

156
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,920
so he left immediately.

157
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,440
He didn't even take his card back.

158
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,520
Good thing

159
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,560
he left us evidence we can use
to track him down.

160
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,800
- It's fake.
- What?

161
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,360
I WENT TO THE ORPHANAGE

162
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:17,520
So, what did you find out?

163
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,640
Aunt Nong.

164
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:23,000
Sin, you're back.

165
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:26,200
Here, taste the <i>kaeng thepho</i> for me.

166
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:28,360
I made it especially for you. Come on.

167
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,840
Try it and tell me if it's too salty.

168
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,160
Come on.

169
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,960
Well.

170
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,600
I completely forgot

171
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,800
you just came back from the hospital
and must be tired.

172
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:50,240
Go sit and rest over there.

173
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:51,840
I'll find something for you to eat.
Come on.

174
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,080
Why did you hide it from me?

175
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,400
Because I knew

176
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,760
that if you found out,
you'd react like this.

177
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:06,040
That's why I didn't want to tell you

178
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,560
that Warat came over for dinner.

179
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,040
It's not just
that he came over for dinner.

180
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,040
Boonsita is dying, Aunt.

181
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,160
Boonsita is dying?

182
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:20,160
Why is she dying?

183
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,520
Why isn't she dead yet?

184
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,920
Why isn't she dead yet?

185
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:28,320
- Aunt, can you listen to me first?
- She…

186
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,240
She…

187
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:32,120
How could she still be alive?

188
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,680
- She must die.
- What are you doing? What's wrong?

189
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,680
Pull yourself together and listen.

190
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,440
What did you do to Kluay?

191
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:43,240
- She should die. She deserves to die.
- Aunt Nong, what did you do to Kluay?

192
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,720
What did you do to Arnon?
What did you do to them?

193
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,520
Tell me. What did you do to them?

194
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,280
Sin.

195
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,440
How could I harm anyone?

196
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:57,440
What's wrong with you, Sin?

197
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,800
- Uh.
- Hm?

198
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,280
How could you treat me like this?

199
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,680
Aren't you afraid you'll shock me?

200
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,400
Aren't you afraid you'll hurt me?

201
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,520
Sin…

202
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,480
There are only the two of us.

203
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,120
You must listen to me.

204
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:23,000
Those people deserve to go to hell.

205
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,000
You should be happy.

206
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,360
But Aunt…

207
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,800
It shouldn't be this way.
This can't be the way.

208
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,080
Yes.

209
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:37,600
It shouldn't be this way.

210
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:39,960
It can't be this way.

211
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,200
Both Arnon

212
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,760
and his woman…

213
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,920
It shouldn't be like this.

214
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,760
- It shouldn't be like this.
- Aunt.

215
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:58,120
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

216
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:07,440
I said she's not eating.
Didn't you hear me?

217
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,160
Don't serve it.

218
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,000
Yes, I know.

219
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,360
But the food still needs to be served.

220
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,560
If you don't want to eat, that's fine.

221
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:18,440
Mr. Warat, please let her do her job.

222
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:22,040
What if something happens
after you eat it?

223
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,760
Go ahead and bring it in.

224
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:26,720
He just recovered from being sick,
so he might say strange things.

225
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,520
Mr. Warat.

226
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,480
Uh.

227
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,680
Don't eat.

228
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:47,480
You shouldn't argue with her like that.

229
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,960
Just let her do her work.

230
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,080
Put yourself in her shoes.
If we don't want to eat,

231
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,080
we just don't eat.

232
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,760
She'll just come collect it later.

233
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:56,120
You went through all that
and you're still this optimistic?

234
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,880
What if there's poison in the food?
You could die.

235
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,280
If you're going to be that fussy,

236
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,600
you might as well take me home.

237
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:05,320
I've wanted to take you home
ever since you woke up.

238
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:08,480
But stay a little longer.

239
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:11,960
Ugh, who would want to stay in a hospital?

240
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,240
I'm only staying
because I'm waiting for Ms. Ampha.

241
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,800
I wonder how she is now.

242
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,600
Right.

243
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:21,280
She came to ask for our help,

244
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,480
but instead,

245
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,640
she ended up helping us
until she was seriously injured.

246
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:27,760
Because she knew we would
face something bad at that house.

247
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,600
True.

248
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,360
She warned us again and again,

249
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,120
but we didn't listen.

250
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:35,280
It's alright, Mr. Warat.

251
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:38,640
If something is beyond our control,

252
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,320
there's nothing we can do anyway.

253
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,280
Whatever is meant to happen will happen.

254
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,760
Not only do you see signs,

255
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,400
you can read people's minds now too.

256
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,120
You're getting more impressive every day.

257
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,680
Of course.

258
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:51,560
No, it's just that

259
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:54,360
I saw you frowning like that,

260
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,440
so I thought it probably wasn't

261
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:57,800
a good feeling.

262
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,840
- Like this.
- Are you mocking me?

263
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,480
No, I'm not mocking you.

264
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,000
When you were hurt,

265
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:08,320
I was really worried.

266
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:12,520
Thank you.

267
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,920
If Ms. Anong really did that,

268
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,800
she'll have to face me.

269
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:31,360
This should definitely
win Mrs. Wanee's favor.

270
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:33,240
You just got out of the hospital,

271
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:36,320
and you're already
rushing back to work. Good.

272
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,520
Actually, today I planned
to spend time with you.

273
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,800
I'm fine now.

274
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,120
Oh, Sin.

275
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,640
You suddenly became such a clingy child.

276
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,120
Go on, go to work.

277
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,680
Chatchai has left
a lot of matters unfinished.

278
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:50,280
I have to take advantage of this moment,

279
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:53,600
while Warat is busy
dealing with Arnon and Kluay,

280
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,080
to recover everything.

281
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:58,800
Sin, you're very capable.

282
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,080
Mrs. Wanee will never dismiss you easily

283
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,720
the way Warat wants.

284
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,760
Yes, Aunt. I'll head back quickly then.

285
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,280
See? So much food.

286
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,280
It's like you're going away for a week.

287
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,599
Didn't you say
you'd only be gone for a short while?

288
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,359
It's just a short while.

289
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,680
But I still want to
take the best care of you.

290
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,920
Why? Isn't that good?

291
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,560
No.

292
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,720
You seem strange.

293
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,760
What's strange about me?

294
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:41,360
If you want to recover quickly,

295
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:44,240
sleep a lot
and take good care of yourself.

296
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:47,320
Forget about everyone else.
Save yourself first.

297
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,320
Are you scolding me?

298
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,720
I'm going now.

299
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,600
Eat a lot so you can grow up quickly.

300
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:57,520
Bye-bye.

301
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:01,960
Grow up quickly?

302
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:03,840
Like I'm a child.

303
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:12,000
Let go. Let go. I'm going to see Kluay,

304
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,600
and I'm going to kill Anong
and Jirasin too.

305
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,720
Calm down, Som.

306
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,960
Ms. Kluay has already gone back
to the Vanich house.

307
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:20,400
Mr. Warat said
you have to listen to him first.

308
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,560
If you don't stop shouting,

309
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:24,080
Mama Toi will definitely find out.

310
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,360
I don't understand.

311
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,960
What kind of enemies are they

312
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:29,120
to go as far as killing each other?

313
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,120
- Let me go.
- Don't, Som.

314
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:33,840
This might not have anything
to do with Jirasin.

315
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:38,960
What?

316
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,520
But I won't dismiss the fact

317
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,160
that Jirasin hates Kluay.

318
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:47,400
I'm thinking the same as you.

319
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,960
The other day, I ran into Jirasin.

320
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:53,520
He said he had nothing to do
with any of this.

321
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:57,480
But you said Kluay saw a sign

322
00:18:57,560 --> 00:19:00,520
that Anong intentionally
tried to harm her, right?

323
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:03,720
That's exactly why I had to come here.

324
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,800
I need to find out

325
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,920
why Ms. Anong tried to harm you

326
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,280
and harm Kluay.

327
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,440
Som,

328
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,480
I need your help with this.

329
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:17,960
Huh? Me?

330
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:19,640
Yes.

331
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:21,960
What are you planning to do?

332
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:30,000
This isn't just some petty thief case?

333
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,360
No, ma'am.

334
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,240
The police have linked this case

335
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:35,200
with the poisoning of Mr. Arnon,
so they believe

336
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,920
there may be something
more complicated behind it.

337
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,640
Do I really need to look at
all these documents?

338
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,360
With the utmost respect,

339
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:45,680
I would like you to.

340
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,920
Boonsita.

341
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,840
The police have gathered evidence

342
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:03,160
on everyone connected to
the stabbing incident involving Mr. Arnon,

343
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:05,400
including Mr. Warat.

344
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:08,440
Kluay was the target of the attacker?

345
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,560
But all of this
is still only a hypothesis, ma'am.

346
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:13,320
My goodness.

347
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,280
Then who exactly

348
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,480
is that girl?

349
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,920
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

350
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,440
I will hurry and gather more information.

351
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,640
This won't do, Supol.

352
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,600
I can't allow Warat

353
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:31,560
to keep risking himself
with these people anymore.

354
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,920
What if one day

355
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,720
he gets caught
in the crossfire like Arnon?

356
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,320
What would we do then?

357
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:42,560
Get Boonsita out of here
as soon as possible.

358
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:46,680
Did you hear me, Supol?

359
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:48,640
Yes, ma'am.

360
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:59,560
Didn't you say
that if your method didn't work,

361
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,080
you would handle it yourself?

362
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,160
What are you talking about?

363
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:04,520
You used it the wrong way.
How can you blame me for that?

364
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,880
I'm not staying to argue with you.
Ridiculous.

365
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:09,280
You asked me to send people
to watch that orphanage,

366
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:11,280
and I did it for you.
What more do you want?

367
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,240
Auntie.

368
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,320
Are you Aunt Anong?

369
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,800
You've mistaken me for someone else.
I don't know you.

370
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,840
My name is Som.

371
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,840
I'm a junior colleague of Sin's at work.

372
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,040
Hello.

373
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:36,960
Hello.

374
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:40,040
I was actually planning
to visit Sin at the hospital,

375
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,200
but I heard he was discharged already.

376
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:44,080
I've seen you at the hospital before.

377
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:48,360
And you work in the same office as Sin,

378
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,920
yet you don't know
he's already back at work?

379
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,920
Oh, really?
We must have just missed each other.

380
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,440
That's fine. Since I came all this way,

381
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:56,600
I'll drive you

382
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,360
- to your house. Come on, Aunt.
- Wait.

383
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,600
- Just get in the car.
- Um…

384
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:01,400
Please get in.

385
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:16,960
The doctor is skilled and very kind too.

386
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,920
Yes, Mr. Warat.

387
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,840
It's not good
to make a patient like me wait so long.

388
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:24,880
I'm around the registration desk.

389
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,520
He's taken the bait, Mr. Warat.

390
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:35,560
Good.

391
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,720
I'm right in front
of Ms. Anong's house now.

392
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,200
Perfect.

393
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:41,360
I'm just worried

394
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,680
Som might not be able
to stall her for long.

395
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:45,320
Don't worry.

396
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,320
We have someone skilled
keeping an eye on Anong.

397
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:50,640
Alright. I'll find a way in.

398
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,040
What exactly is going on here?

399
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:14,240
I already told you
I was going to visit Sin

400
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,360
and then take you home.

401
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,400
But this isn't the road to my house.

402
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,960
You've already driven me far away.

403
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,720
Where exactly are you taking me?

404
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:22,960
Stop the car right now.

405
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:35,240
Oh? Did your phone fall, Auntie?

406
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,640
It's okay. I'll pick it up when we arrive.

407
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:39,240
No. Stop the car.

408
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:43,000
How can I stop now?
There are cars behind us.

409
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,880
And there's your phone too.

410
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:47,680
Or should I keep it for you?

411
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:55,000
SLOW DOWN

412
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:01,320
Why aren't you making a U-turn?
Where are you turning?

413
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:03,640
Oh, I'm sorry.

414
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,800
I must have taken the wrong turn.

415
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,760
And there's no place to turn back either.

416
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,440
I'm so sorry.

417
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,800
Who exactly are you people?

418
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:34,520
<i>Kluay</i>

419
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,400
<i>was the target of the attacker?</i>

420
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,320
So, that's why.

421
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:41,240
That's why no one wanted me
to go back to Baan Saeng.

422
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,760
<i>Don't worry about being hungry.</i>

423
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,080
Didn't you say
you'd only be gone for a short while?

424
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:53,080
It's just a short while. But I still
want to take the best care of you.

425
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:56,120
Then Mr. Warat must know about this too.

426
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,320
You really fooled me, Mr. Warat.

427
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:06,480
I understand now

428
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:09,000
why Grandma
never wanted me to be close to Mr. Warat.

429
00:25:09,960 --> 00:25:11,440
Oh, Kluay.

430
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,040
Everything's all set, Pong?

431
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:28,120
<i>Mr. Sin will come to</i>
<i>the company tomorrow, Non.</i>

432
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,160
You're quite ruthless, Mr. Warat.

433
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,480
Turn the baby toward me.

434
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,360
Alright.

435
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,840
My daughter…

436
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:56,960
You…

437
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,480
So this is where you've been hiding.

438
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:10,720
Boonsita.

439
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:12,840
Everyone has been
looking for you everywhere.

440
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,680
Madam wants you to take
some medicine and go upstairs to rest.

441
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,680
Oh, it was just a little rain.

442
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:34,920
I'm not seriously ill.
Please take it away.

443
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:40,080
It's fine. I'll talk to her myself.

444
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,240
Alright.

445
00:27:47,120 --> 00:27:49,280
Why didn't you do as I told you?

446
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:50,640
Uh…

447
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:55,600
I'm grateful for your kindness, Grandma,

448
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:59,560
but I'm not seriously ill,
so I didn't want

449
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,440
to take medicine unnecessarily.

450
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,600
I just saw that you were unwell,

451
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:07,520
and I didn't want you
getting sick again in my house.

452
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,440
I'm sorry.

453
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,880
And when Warat returns,

454
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,560
tell someone to inform me.

455
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:15,160
I have something
to discuss with both of you.

456
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,200
Uh, Grandma…

457
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,040
There's something I'd like to talk about.

458
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:24,960
It's about this painting.

459
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:32,680
Who allowed you
to bring this painting back here?

460
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:35,920
This painting was painted
over the original one.

461
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:36,840
I didn't ask,

462
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:39,200
and I don't want to know.

463
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,120
Have someone return this painting

464
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,880
to the Rose arbor house immediately.

465
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:45,600
Uh, well.

466
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:49,440
The original painting
was not of an empty chair.

467
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,120
It was actually

468
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:54,680
a woman holding a child.

469
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:59,520
I know

470
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,760
that Mr. Wichan painted this picture.

471
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:04,760
And the woman in the painting

472
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:08,000
is Ms. Ampha and her daughter.

473
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:11,080
Who gave you permission
to talk about such things in my house?

474
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,640
Well…

475
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:14,680
I wanted to tell you, Grandma,

476
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:17,280
about the past vision I saw.

477
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,160
Okay. I can sense

478
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:22,080
that both Mr. Wichan
and Ms. Ampha have already died.

479
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:24,040
But the little girl in the painting…

480
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,840
She is still alive.

481
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,440
These two must be
sleeping in separate rooms.

482
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,800
<i>These are secretly taken photos.</i>

483
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,040
He still hasn't come.

484
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:39,400
This is no good.

485
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,960
Or did he already go home?

486
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,640
Mr. Warat, come out right now.

487
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:50,920
Mr. Sarut didn't fall for our trap.
I was mistaken.

488
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,640
I can't. I can't go out right now.

489
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:56,000
I found something
about myself and my mother.

490
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,080
Just come out right now.

491
00:30:58,160 --> 00:30:59,200
It's urgent.

492
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:03,160
Mr. Warat, don't do this.

493
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:06,880
Um, excuse me.

494
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,720
The man named Mr. Sarut

495
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,960
who just paid a moment ago,

496
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,400
- he…
- Oh.

497
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:14,240
Mr. Sarut? Is something wrong?

498
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:16,760
Actually…

499
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:22,800
Nothing. Thank you very much.

500
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,200
<i>It's okay now.</i>

501
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,800
<i>I found Mr. Sarut.</i>

502
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:31,480
<i>Okay, Mr. Arnon.</i>

503
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:32,880
<i>We'll talk later. Gotta go.</i>

504
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,680
Aunt Nong.

505
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:47,240
Where did everyone go? Aunt Nong?

506
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:51,720
Chatchai?

507
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:54,240
Why are you calling?

508
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,120
Didn't I tell you already?
If the documents aren't ready,

509
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,320
you'll have to go to Chiang Mai alone.
I'm not wasting my time going with you.

510
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,000
Enough. Stop talking. I'm home now.

511
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:05,560
I'm taking Aunt Nong to see a doctor.

512
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,400
Please make an appointment
with your friend for me.

513
00:32:08,680 --> 00:32:09,800
Thank you.

514
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:14,280
Aunt Nong. Aunt Nong.

515
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:18,360
Aunt Nong.

516
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:27,840
Mr. Sarut.

517
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:29,840
Oh, Mr. Arnon.

518
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:34,200
These days,
everyone goes to see a psychiatrist.

519
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:35,840
It's not unusual anymore.

520
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:37,240
Do you want me
to talk to your aunt for you?

521
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:38,760
Aunt Nong.

522
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:45,680
Aunt Nong.

523
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,880
- How did you get in here?
- Oh?

524
00:32:57,880 --> 00:32:59,320
I walked in.
What kind of question is that?

525
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,400
That's not funny.

526
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,440
This is my house. It's not
a place where anyone can just walk in.

527
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:04,040
Ugh.

528
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:06,320
Jirasin,

529
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:08,280
have you ever thought positively
about people at all?

530
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,160
I had an appointment with Mr. Sarut.

531
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,760
I came early.

532
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:14,440
The door was open,
so I just walked in. That's all.

533
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:17,720
Then what were you doing in the kitchen?
You seemed busy.

534
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:19,440
Didn't you think no one was home?

535
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,920
Then how did you know
I was in the kitchen?

536
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,880
Here we go again.

537
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:24,880
How many rooms does this house have?

538
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:26,600
There's a kitchen and a bathroom.

539
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:28,720
If you were in the bathroom,
that wouldn't make sense, would it?

540
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:31,000
You sure know
every corner of this house well.

541
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:33,520
Jirasin, this is my second time here.

542
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,920
Okay, if you don't want me here,
I can leave.

543
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,440
You're not going anywhere.

544
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:40,880
I'm calling Uncle Rut.

545
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:45,200
I want to know what important appointment
made him invite a major businessman here.

546
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:55,600
What?

547
00:33:57,520 --> 00:33:59,440
Mr. Warat wanted to see me that badly?

548
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:01,880
- Yes.
- Oh.

549
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,040
Excuse me.

550
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:06,320
Oh, Sin?

551
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,920
He never calls.

552
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:13,159
Hello? Yeah, what is it, Sin?

553
00:34:13,239 --> 00:34:15,719
What? Warat is at the house?

554
00:34:17,239 --> 00:34:19,040
Yes. He's at the house right now.

555
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:21,760
He said he had an appointment with you.

556
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:24,800
But as far as I know, Aunt Nong said

557
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:27,320
you would be at physical therapy all day.

558
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:28,880
You shouldn't have been able
to invite anyone to the house.

559
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,560
Warat made an appointment with me?

560
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:32,639
Yes. I found him sitting in the house

561
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:34,360
even though no one was home.

562
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:36,000
And I don't know how he got in.

563
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:37,199
Jirasin, I…

564
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,800
Oh right, right, right. Listen.

565
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,320
<i>That's right, just like you understood.</i>

566
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:44,520
Then why did you talk like

567
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:45,639
you didn't make any appointment with him?

568
00:34:45,719 --> 00:34:48,040
<i>You said Warat</i>

569
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:51,159
<i>made an appointment with me.</i>
<i>That's not it.</i>

570
00:34:51,239 --> 00:34:55,040
Actually, I was the one who invited him.

571
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,600
That's it.

572
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,280
See? Do you believe me now?

573
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:09,520
I told you I had an appointment.
What a mood killer.

574
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,480
Otherwise, I wouldn't have come
and wasted my time.

575
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:12,560
Hold on.

576
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:16,640
When you visit other people's houses,

577
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:18,440
do you normally
wear shoes into their houses?

578
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,560
It's nothing. I was just asking.

579
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,640
I don't need an answer.

580
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:31,920
I'm leaving. Bye.

581
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:40,400
Why did he come here?

582
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,480
This is insane.

583
00:35:56,440 --> 00:35:58,640
Praewilai. Warat.

584
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:02,880
Could it be that he already knows?

585
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:07,760
Good thing you told me first
that Mr. Warat went to the house.

586
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:12,160
He likes surprising people.
Sometimes he leaves me waiting for hours.

587
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,400
What should we do now?

588
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,920
I think we should split up for now.

589
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:18,480
- Mr. Warat looked very upset.
- Oh.

590
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,280
Anyway,

591
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:22,360
please apologize to Mr. Warat for me.

592
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:23,840
- Sure.
- Mm.

593
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,760
Or should I call
and apologize to Mr. Warat right now?

594
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:33,160
No need. When he gets angry,
he gets over it on his own.

595
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:34,840
Alright, alright.

596
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:48,400
He must have gotten the photo
from this room.

597
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:52,400
What are you doing in my room, Jirasin?

598
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:54,880
I'm the one who should be asking you that.

599
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,120
Were you searching my room?

600
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:05,280
It's because you think like this
that he tricked you so easily.

601
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,440
Sin.

602
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:08,600
This is too much.

603
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,800
I'm running out of patience with you.

604
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:14,000
Warat dropped this photo.

605
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:17,000
Do you really believe
that he came here just to see you?

606
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:18,880
Why would he lie to me?

607
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:20,920
I don't know. But what I do know

608
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,600
is that he got this photo from this room.

609
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:25,600
Don't tell me this photo isn't yours.

610
00:37:30,160 --> 00:37:31,640
Let me ask you honestly.

611
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:35,640
Why do you hate Warat so much?

612
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:37,880
Do you want him and me
to turn against each other?

613
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:40,280
Oh, Uncle, this is exactly how you are.

614
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:42,760
They say some people
are impossible to talk to, this is why.

615
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:44,560
Because they just
don't understand anything.

616
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,200
Then tell me.
Where did you get this photo?

617
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,400
Go ask your beloved child.

618
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:00,640
The reason Ms. Ampha ended up like this

619
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:03,160
- is because of me.
- If you still refuse to stop

620
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:05,440
bringing up that woman's name,

621
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:07,720
<i>you will no longer stay in this house.</i>

622
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:10,120
I want to know how he's connected to me.

623
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:13,400
But are you sure
you can accept the answer?

624
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:15,160
NEXT EPISODE

625
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:16,480
<i>I want to know too</i>

626
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,800
how Kluay and Anong are connected.

627
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,600
<i>Mr. Arnon</i>
<i>was just caught in the crossfire.</i>

628
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:26,640
<i>The one she really wanted to kill</i>

629
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:29,080
was me.

630
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:32,360
<i>If everything goes as we think,</i>

631
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:33,840
<i>then it means</i>

632
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:35,760
Kluay is the daughter of…

633
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:03,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
